BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (The Digital Clutter Crisis) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (We live in an unprecedented era of digital overload. The average person checks their phone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (96 times per day, has 40 apps installed, receives 121 emails daily, and spends over 7) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (hours per day on screens. This constant digital stimulation creates chronic stress,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (reduces attention spans, hampers creativity, and leaves us feeling perpetually behind.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (Digital clutter is just as draining as physical clutter, yet most people never address it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (Overflowing inboxes, chaotic file systems, endless notification pings, and cluttered) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (desktops create a low-grade anxiety that saps your energy and focus throughout the day.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 512.8 Td (This workbook provides a systematic approach to decluttering every aspect of your digital) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 498.8 Td (life and building sustainable habits that keep it organized permanently.) Tj ET
