54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (The Inbox Zero Philosophy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Inbox Zero does not mean you have zero emails in your inbox at all times. It means your) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (inbox is a processing station, not a storage system. Every email that comes in gets) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (processed \(reply, archive, delegate, delete, or defer\) rather than sitting there creating) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (mental clutter and guilt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (The goal is to check email intentionally at scheduled times, process everything that came) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (in, and then close your email until the next scheduled check. This eliminates the constant) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (low-grade anxiety of an overflowing inbox and the productivity-killing habit of checking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (email every few minutes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 492.8 Td (Step 1: The Great Email Purge) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 465.0 Td (If you have hundreds or thousands of unread emails, do not try to read them all. Use this) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 451.0 Td (triage approach:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 427.2 Td (- Select all emails older than 30 days and ARCHIVE them \(not delete\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 413.2 Td (- If anything was truly urgent from 30+ days ago, someone would have followed up) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 399.2 Td (- Search for and delete all promotional emails in bulk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 385.2 Td (- Unsubscribe from every newsletter you have not read in the past month) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 371.2 Td (- Create a TEMP folder and move remaining old emails there for later review) Tj ET
